# Go conventions

- Don’t assume. Don’t hide confusion. Surface tradeoffs.
- Minimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.
- Touch only what you must. Clean up only your own mess.
- Define success criteria. Loop until verified.
- Match existing package layout under `internal/`; keep `cmd/satip-lab` thin (flags + wiring only).
- Prefer stdlib; new dependencies need justification in PR text.
- Use table-driven tests in `*_test.go`; integration tests for HTTP/RTSP go in `internal/simulator/`.
- Never block the main goroutine on infinite TS loops — use tickers/delays in `internal/ts`.
- Guard shared session state with `sync.Mutex` (see `internal/rtsp/server.go`).
- After changing `go.mod` minimum version, update `Dockerfile` golang image and `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.
- Run `make test` and `make lint` before finishing.
